<h2>
    Description
</h2>

<p>
    Y.soon accepts a callback function to be called as soon as possible in a future turn of the JavaScript event loop.  Y.soon(fn); will attempt to be faster and more efficient than Y.later(0, this, fn);
    but it falls back to Y.later in worst case.
</p>
<p>
    This functionality is not natively implemented in most browsers so various tricks are used to emulated it.  Much of this is based on setImmediate.js.  https://github.com/NobleJS/setImmediate
</p>
